CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Director C. W. Berry, seated at the center of the table, confers with his staff in the council hall.  The staff consists of a secretary, registered nurse, three life guards and 22 trained counsellors..."
TitMainTitle: Camp Director C. W. Berry seated at head of table, meeting with staff in the Council Hall at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
